            "answer_text": "Let the present ages of the two persons be 3x and 2x. Ten years ago their ages were (3x-10) and (2x-10). The ratio their ages 10 years ago was (3x-10):(2x-10) = 2:1, or 2*(2x-10) = 1*(3x-10), or 4x-20 = 3x - 10, or 4x-3x = x = 20\u201310 =10 So the two are 30 and 20 years old, now. After 5 years the ratio of their ages will be (30+5):(20+5) = 35:25 = 7:5. Answer. ",
